红葡萄酒和白兰地后
claret and slivovitz.

177
00:12:50,182 --> 00:12:51,422
根本不是什么好主意
Not a good idea at all.

178
00:12:55,742 --> 00:12:57,420
你无所不知 Antoni
You know everything, Antoni.

179
00:12:57,421 --> 00:13:00,302
跟她生活在一起的那个俄罗斯人是什么来历?
What's the story with this Russian she lives with?

180
00:13:02,582 --> 00:13:04,302
Maxim Mostov 白俄罗斯人
Maxim Mostov. White Russian.

181
00:13:05,462 --> 00:13:09,020
自从他离开家乡后他云游四方
He's lived in many places since he left his homeland.

182
00:13:09,021 --> 00:13:11,453
他是一个政治记者
He makes a living as a political journalist.

183
00:13:11,454 --> 00:13:12,780
主要攻击斯大林的
Mostly attacking Stalin.

184
00:13:12,781 --> 00:13:14,982
话多 喝的更多
Talks too much and drinks even more.

185
00:13:15,398 --> 00:13:16,367
为什么她和他在一起?   
Why is she with him?  

186
00:13:16,952 --> 00:13:18,661
谁懂女人呢?
Who knows with women?

187
00:13:18,662 --> 00:13:20,582
他们在一起多久了
How long have they been together?

188
00:13:22,628 --> 00:13:24,921
够长了 你就在想这些么  
Long enough, is that what you are thinking? 

189
00:13:25,795 --> 00:13:26,422
小心为妙啊 我的朋友
Careful, my friend.

190
00:13:36,342 --> 00:13:37,461
已经3点半了  
It's 3.30. 

191
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:38,980
我答应过不能太晚带你回家的
I was told not to bring you back too late.

192
00:13:38,981 --> 00:13:42,342
Max估计已经睡了  不必费心送我上楼了
Max will be asleep. Don't bother to see me upstairs.

193
00:13:43,662 --> 00:13:45,862
还有 感谢你 这是个难忘的夜晚
And thank you for a memorable evening.

194
00:15:08,542 --> 00:15:09,582
来杯咖啡 
Coffee, please.

195
00:15:11,782 --> 00:15:15,662
给这位女士来杯巧克力
And another chocolate for Madame.

196
00:15:16,822 --> 00:15:19,541
总是这么准时啊 上校
Always so punctual, Colonel.

197
00:15:19,542 --> 00:15:22,382
你跟Uhl先生约会准时么
Were you on time for your rendezvous with Herr Uhl?

198
00:15:22,383 --> 00:15:25,661
伯爵夫人总是姗姗来迟
For him the Countess is always late.

199
00:15:25,662 --> 00:15:30,501
她有时不太随和 我相当喜欢她
She can be difficult at times. I rather like her.

200
00:15:30,502 --> 00:15:33,021
当然 他认为她是身无分文的
Of course he thinks she's penniless.

201
00:15:33,579 --> 00:15:35,019
他又借给她一些你的钱了  
He loaned her some more of your money. 

202
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:36,181
你想把钱收回来么
Do you want it back?

203
00:15:36,548 --> 00:15:37,710
留着吧 Olga  
No keep it, Olga. 

204
00:15:37,710 --> 00:15:40,061
我们已经按惯例为你存了款
We've made your usual deposit.

205
00:15:40,062 --> 00:15:42,174
我们对你所做的一切感激在心
We're appreciative of what you do.

206
00:15:42,175 --> 00:15:44,100
也许我生来就是个间谍
Perhaps I was born to be a spy.

207
00:15:44,101 --> 00:15:45,902
我们得适应我们所处的时代
We adapt to the times we live in.

208
00:15:46,942 --> 00:15:48,340
法国有句俗语
There's a French saying,

209
00:15:48,341 --> 00:15:52,300
"神随意栽种 人自求繁荣"
"Wherever God has planted you, you must know how to flower."

210
00:15:52,301 --> 00:15:55,262
这对之前的事情无疑是种促进
It's certainly an improvement on what came before.

211
00:15:58,422 --> 00:16:00,221
你是怎么找到Uhl先生的?
How did you find Herr Uhl?

212
00:16:00,222 --> 00:16:03,180
每次华沙之行都是他生命的极乐时刻
His trips to Warsaw are the high points of his life.

213
00:16:03,181 --> 00:16:06,102
另外他工作在外 是个顾家的好男人
Otherwise he labours away, the good family man.

214
00:16:07,102 --> 00:16:08,569
他下个月会再来  
He'll be back next month. 

215
00:16:08,569 --> 00:16:10,542
尽管有些不情愿
Though he showed some reluctance.

216
00:16:10,543 --> 00:16:12,218
哦 他会回来的  
Oh, he'll come. 

217
00:16:13,029 --> 00:16:15,062
他甚至可能已经爱上伯爵夫人了
He may even be in love with the Countess.

218
00:16:16,222 --> 00:16:18,222
我是不是演过头了
Am I overplaying my part?

219
00:17:03,142 --> 00:17:04,262
我的围巾 我落车上了
My scarf, I left it.

220
00:17:10,382 --> 00:17:12,502
- 该死 这些人   - 请让我进去
- Fuck these people.  - Please!

221
00:17:13,662 --> 00:17:14,742
没到时候
Not yet.

222
00:17:18,422 --> 00:17:19,582
就现在
Now.

223
00:18:24,182 --> 00:18:26,821
他们在外面还有巡逻
They still have patrols out there.

224
00:18:26,822 --> 00:18:29,901
下一轮巡逻过来是在9点25分
The next one comes through at 9.35.

225
00:18:29,902 --> 00:18:33,181
他们总是那么准时么?   - 分毫不差
They're always prompt?  - Like a clock.

226
00:18:33,182 --> 00:18:35,390
- 带着狗?   - 一直是  
- Dogs?  - Always. 

227
00:18:36,759 --> 00:18:38,061
你确定要这么做 中校?
Sure you want to do this, Colonel?

228
00:18:38,062 --> 00:18:41,341
要是他们看到你 会当场开枪的
If they see you they'll shoot on sight.

229
00:18:41,342 --> 00:18:43,502
如果我们不出来 在车上动点手脚就没事
If we don't show up, do something with the car.

230
00:19:22,942 --> 00:19:24,742
还好吧?   - 我没事
All right?  - I'm OK.

231
00:19:43,102 --> 00:19:44,142
这是什么
What is it?

232
00:19:45,262 --> 00:19:47,222
是一个坦克的陷阱
It's a tank trap.

233
00:19:51,116 --> 00:19:52,383
为什么他们要覆盖他们的坦克陷阱?  
Why are they covering their tank traps? 

234
00:19:52,383 --> 00:19:53,423
这没道理啊
That doesn't make sense.

235
00:20:07,542 --> 00:20:09,342
往光源处打
Go for the light.

236
00:20:11,782 --> 00:20:13,742
走 走 快走 快 快!
Go, go, go, go, go!

237
00:21:14,782 --> 00:21:17,061
我昨晚在找你
I looked for you last night.

238
00:21:17,062 --> 00:21:19,860
你是不是忘记了王子和我要举办一个晚会?
Did you forget the Prince and I were holding a soiree?

239
00:21:19,861 --> 00:21:22,403
昨晚实难抽身 公主  
It was impossible to get away, Princess. 

240
00:21:22,403 --> 00:21:23,582
文书工作堆积如山
Paperwork. Reams of it.

241
00:21:24,582 --> 00:21:28,102
嗯 这又是什么 纸划伤的?
Hmm, and what's this, a paper cut?

242
00:21:34,462 --> 00:21:36,101
我读了你的报告
I read your report.

243
00:21:36,102 --> 00:21:38,900
- 看上去真是千钧一发   - 我很幸运
- A near miss by the sound of it.  - I was fortunate.

244
00:21:38,901 --> 00:21:41,633
如果被抓了呢  要是你射到某人了呢?
What if you were caught? Or you'd shot someone?

245
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:43,066
天哪 那我们要如何解释?   
Christ, how would we explain that?  

246
00:21:43,066 --> 00:21:44,220
我并没有那样做 也没有人那么做
I wasn't. And no-one was.

247
00:21:44,221 --> 00:21:45,780
巴黎将会持怀疑态度的
Paris will take a dim view of this.

248
00:21:45,781 --> 00:21:48,022
你做什么 你想试着证明什么
What are you, what are you trying to prove?

249
00:21:48,023 --> 00:21:50,381
我想我已经解释明白了
I thought I made that clear.

250
00:21:50,382 --> 00:21:51,927
他们覆盖了陷阱 
They're covering traps 

251
00:21:51,927 --> 00:21:53,620
这样他们自己的坦克便不会受到阻碍
so their own tanks won't be impeded.

252
00:21:53,621 --> 00:21:55,212
你的意思是如果他们入侵   
If they invade, you mean. 

253
00:21:55,655 --> 00:21:56,260
希特勒铁了心要发动战争
Hitler is intent on war,

254
00:21:56,872 --> 00:21:57,419
唯一的问题是
it's only a question of 

255
00:21:57,419 --> 00:21:58,942
他会先攻打谁
who he picks a fight with first.

256
00:22:05,182 --> 00:22:07,782
亲爱的中校  日子过的如何
Dear Colonel! How has life been treating you?

257
00:22:07,783 --> 00:22:10,821
非常好 Rozen女士  你们二位呢
Very well, Madame Rozen. And yourselves?

258
00:22:10,822 --> 00:22:13,102
本应更好些 但是我们没法抱怨什么
Could be better, but we can't complain.

259
00:22:18,342 --> 00:22:19,622
他是你的朋友么
Is he a friend of yours?

260
00:22:19,623 --> 00:22:23,501
不算是  一个同胞 但是是个流亡者
Not exactly. A compatriot, but an emigre.

261
00:22:23,942 --> 00:22:25,867
一些人放弃了我们 是多么的悲哀啊  
Sad how some people abandon us. 

262
00:22:25,867 --> 00:22:26,902
一部分是最聪明的人啊
Some of the brightest.

263
00:22:26,903 --> 00:22:30,621
不是每个人都想建设社会主义的 亲爱的
Not everyone wants to build socialism, my love.

264
00:22:30,622 --> 00:22:32,138
嗯 在我们的家乡
Well, it isn't an easy life,

265
00:22:32,139 --> 00:22:34,142
生活着实不易 为什么不承认呢
where we come from, why not admit it?

266
00:22:34,143 --> 00:22:35,566
但是 中校 
But, Colonel, 

267
00:22:36,012 --> 00:22:38,074
比起我们之前的生活好多了
better than what we had before.

268
00:22:38,074 --> 00:22:38,826
失陪了
Excuse me.

269
00:22:49,142 --> 00:22:50,381
Anna
Anna.

270
00:22:50,382 --> 00:22:52,182
我知道你觉得这类场合很无聊
I know you find these occasions boring

271
00:22:52,183 --> 00:22:54,941
但是 我已经开始乐在其中了
but I'm beginning to enjoy them.

272
00:22:54,942 --> 00:22:56,340
或者是享受香槟?
Or is it the champagne?

273
00:22:56,341 --> 00:22:57,582
香槟确实有帮助
The champagne helps.

274
00:22:59,305 --> 00:23:00,893
所以你认识Rozen夫妇   
So you know the Rozens. 

275
00:23:00,893 --> 00:23:01,662
每个人都知道他们
Everyone knows them.

276
00:23:01,663 --> 00:23:03,821
他们试图拉拢你吗
Do they try to recruit you?

277
00:23:03,822 --> 00:23:05,397
Max说俄罗斯大使馆的
Max says everyone at the

278
00:23:05,398 --> 00:23:08,220
每一个人都是间谍 即使看门人也是
Russian Embassy is a spy, even the janitor.

279
00:23:08,221 --> 00:23:10,980
嗯 Malka时常想给我煮些罗宋汤
Well, Malka offers to cook me borscht from time to time.

280
00:23:10,981 --> 00:23:14,702
他们当然鄙视Max 因为他的文章
They despise Max of course, because of what he writes.

281
00:23:14,703 --> 00:23:19,101
距离俄罗斯进行试验时日不多了...
It's not so far from the Russian experiment...

282
00:23:19,102 --> 00:23:21,112
我最好把他带回家  
I'd better get him home. 

283
00:23:21,594 --> 00:23:22,822
他让美国大使走投无路了
He's cornered the American Ambassador.

284
00:23:25,422 --> 00:23:27,854
你们这些美国人听到"社会主义" 
You Americans go weak at the knees 

285
00:23:27,854 --> 00:23:28,540
腿都软了
when you hear the word "Socialism"

286
00:23:28,541 --> 00:23:31,262
你还能叫它什么
But what else can you call it?

287
00:23:44,902 --> 00:23:47,181
为什么她和这个俄罗斯人在一起
Why is she with this Russian?

288
00:23:47,616 --> 00:23:48,549
你讨厌俄罗斯人就跟
You hate Russians 

289
00:23:48,549 --> 00:23:49,742
讨厌德国人一样吧 Marek?
as much as Germans, Marek?

290
00:23:51,342 --> 00:23:54,862
别无选择  一个在东边 一个在西边
Nothing to choose. One to the east, one to the west.

291
00:23:55,862 --> 00:23:58,342
两边都希望像敲核桃一样侵入波兰
Both waiting to crush Poland like a walnut.

292
00:24:00,422 --> 00:24:02,519
你想去哪儿 头儿?  
You wish to go on somewhere, boss? 

293
00:24:02,519 --> 00:24:03,782
餐馆还是夜总会?
Restaurant? Nightclub?

294
00:24:06,342 --> 00:24:09,222
不 我想回家 把这该死的领结脱下来
No, I want to go home and get this bloody collar off.

295
00:24:40,062 --> 00:24:43,002
伯爵夫人 自从你向我介绍
Countess, since you introduced

296
00:24:43,003 --> 00:24:47,022
那个法国人 我的生命就发生了改变
me to the Frenchman, my life has changed.

297
00:24:48,702 --> 00:24:52,181
当然 这使得我们关系更加密切 
It has brought us closer, of course,

298
00:24:52,182 --> 00:24:54,574
但是 我陷入了一个
but, I am caught up in a

299
00:24:54,575 --> 00:24:59,061
危险的游戏 这是个危险的时代
dangerous game and these are dangerous times.

300
00:24:59,062 --> 00:25:00,348
你不希望再见到我了么   
You don't wish to see me again?  

301
00:25:00,850 --> 00:25:02,022
哦 不 当然不是喽
Oh, no, of course I do.

302
00:25:03,102 --> 00:25:05,022
你知道我对你的感情
You know how I feel about you.

303
00:25:06,822 --> 00:25:09,302
但是也许我们不得不考虑一下我们的将来
But perhaps we have to think of our future.

304
00:25:10,382 --> 00:25:11,422
在一起么?
Together?

305
00:25:12,862 --> 00:25:13,982
为什么不呢
Why not?

306
00:25:16,022 --> 00:25:18,982
Edvard 我已经逃离了故土
Edvard, I have already fled the country of my birth.

307
00:25:18,983 --> 00:25:22,422
我已经不知道哪里会安全了
I don't know where is safe any more.

308
00:25:26,582 --> 00:25:29,142
和我在一起就安全了
Safe would be with me.

309
00:25:51,782 --> 00:25:52,822
都在这了
Here it is.

310
00:25:59,142 --> 00:26:02,742
最后的设计图应该在下个月就会完成
The final blueprints should be complete by next month.

311
00:26:02,743 --> 00:26:05,221
那么我们下次就到那时候见
Then that's when we'll meet next.

312
00:26:05,222 --> 00:26:07,101
啊 这恐怕很难
Ah, that's difficult.

313
00:26:07,575 --> 00:26:09,395
8号我和其他两名工程师
On the eighth me and two other engineers,

314
00:26:09,395 --> 00:26:12,398
我们必须去施兰贝格的黑森林   
we have to go to Schramberg in the Black Forest.  

315
00:26:09,657 --> 00:26:12,169
{\pos(192,26)}施兰贝格：德国巴登-符腾堡州的一个市镇

316
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,257
去干什么
What for?

317
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:14,500
去观察坦克演习
To observe tank exercises.

318
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,422
我们被要求提供建议
We're being asked for our recommendations.

319
00:26:16,423 --> 00:26:18,581
演习?  你指的是军事演习?
Exercises? You mean manoeuvres?

320
00:26:19,087 --> 00:26:21,189
军事演戏 是的 我是这么猜想的
Manoeuvres, yes, I suppose so.

321
00:26:21,189 --> 00:26:23,314
坦克不会进森林的吧 Uhl先生  
Tanks don't go in forests, Herr Uhl. 

322
00:26:23,314 --> 00:26:25,232
森林里有树
There are trees in forests.

323
00:26:26,401 --> 00:26:28,531
我不是军人  
I'm not a military man. 

324
00:26:28,531 --> 00:26:30,462
我怎么知道他们在做些什么?
How would I know what they're up to?

325
00:26:33,462 --> 00:26:34,862
我们一周后见
Let's meet a week later.

326
00:26:35,942 --> 00:26:40,381
我会的  但是从此我们交易结束
I will do that. But then it ends.

327
00:26:40,382 --> 00:26:42,845
上次 盖世太保在边界上  
Last time, the Gestapo were at the border. 

328
00:26:42,845 --> 00:26:43,961
我不得不躲开他们
I had to elude them,

329
00:26:43,961 --> 00:26:44,756
从铁轨上爬下来 
scramble down the tracks 

330
00:26:44,756 --> 00:26:45,740
然后乘出租车去下一站
and take a taxi to the next station.

331
00:26:45,741 --> 00:26:47,060
你在怕什么
What were you frightened of?

332
00:26:47,061 --> 00:26:49,780
如果他们问我 我在华沙做什么
What if they asked me what I was doing in Warsaw?!

333
00:26:49,781 --> 00:26:51,620
告诉他们你去和一位女士幽会
Tell them you were seeing a lady.

334
00:26:51,621 --> 00:26:53,182
通奸还不算犯罪
Adultery is not yet a crime.

335
00:27:14,822 --> 00:27:16,541
Uhl先生?
Herr Uhl?

336
00:27:16,542 --> 00:27:17,582
是的?
Yes?

337
00:27:18,742 --> 00:27:21,021
我是Renata  伯爵夫人的侄女
I'm Renata. The Countess's niece.

338
00:27:21,022 --> 00:27:24,982
她想让我在你去车站前找到你
She wanted me to catch you before you went to the station.

339
00:27:24,983 --> 00:27:27,381
她是不是身体不太好   - 不 不 不
Is she unwell?  - No, no, no.

340
00:27:27,382 --> 00:27:30,102
她说有重要的事要告诉你
She says it's important that she tells you something

341
00:27:30,103 --> 00:27:32,062
在你上火车前
before you catch your train.

342
00:28:10,582 --> 00:28:13,821
- 那女孩是谁   - 什么女孩
- Who is the girl? - What girl?

343
00:28:13,822 --> 00:28:15,180
见过你线人的金发女郎   
The blonde who met your man. 

344
00:28:16,095 --> 00:28:17,009
他跟她走了
He went off with her.

345
00:28:17,422 --> 00:28:19,582
不好责怪他 她长的很漂亮
Hard to blame him, she was very pretty.

346
00:28:19,583 --> 00:28:21,021
她是妓女么
Was she a prostitute?

347
00:28:21,022 --> 00:28:22,702
为什么在他跟他的伯爵夫人共度春宵后
Why would he want a tart 

348
00:28:22,702 --> 00:28:24,182
还想要一个妓女?
after a night with his Countess?

349
00:28:25,422 --> 00:28:26,782
他们朝哪个方向去了?
Which way did they go?

350
00:28:26,783 --> 00:28:28,701
朝Muranow区
Towards Muranow.

351
00:28:28,702 --> 00:28:29,862
我们去跟着他们
Let's get after them.

352
00:29:08,542 --> 00:29:09,982
伯爵夫人住这儿?
The Countess lives here?

353
00:29:10,982 --> 00:29:12,996
她告诉我没有你的帮助
She tells me without your help 

354
00:29:13,542 --> 00:29:14,342
事情会变得更糟糕
it would be somewhere worse.

355
00:30:22,502 --> 00:30:24,742
我觉得不妙  有些不对劲
I don't like this. Something isn't right.

356
00:30:39,822 --> 00:30:40,862
发生了什么
What's going on?

357
00:30:40,863 --> 00:30:42,341
这个人病了
The man is sick.

358
00:30:42,342 --> 00:30:44,182
他没病 他被麻醉了
He's not sick, he's drugged.

359
00:31:14,902 --> 00:31:16,501
是三氯甲烷
It's chloroform.

360
00:31:16,502 --> 00:31:17,861
他死了么
Is he dead?

361
00:31:17,862 --> 00:31:18,981
还有脉搏
There's a pulse.

362
00:31:18,982 --> 00:31:20,662
很微弱 但是还有
It's faint, but it's there.

363
00:31:23,102 --> 00:31:26,180
公共场合的绑架 街头斗殴
An abduction in public, brawling in the streets!

364
00:31:26,181 --> 00:31:28,220
难道我们希望早报上出现这些么?
Are we to look forward to this in the morning papers?

365
00:31:28,221 --> 00:31:29,667
不 Jourdain 
No, Jourdain, 

366
00:31:29,667 --> 00:31:30,782
我来打几个电话掩盖掉这件事
I made some calls and put the lid on it.

367
00:31:30,783 --> 00:31:32,101
这个人是谁
Who was this man?

368
00:31:32,102 --> 00:31:33,221
一个线人
A contact.

369
00:31:33,222 --> 00:31:35,341
你是说他是间谍 他还活着么?
You mean a spy. Will he live?

370
00:31:35,342 --> 00:31:37,340
是的 但是他不能回德国了
Yes, but he can't go back to Germany.

371
00:31:37,341 --> 00:31:38,298
我会向他保证
I'd like to assure him

372
00:31:38,299 --> 00:31:40,302
我们能帮助他重新安置下来
that we can help with some kind of relocation.

373
00:31:40,303 --> 00:31:41,661
基于什么理由
On what grounds?

374
00:31:41,662 --> 00:31:42,982
他应得的
He's earned it.

375
00:31:44,022 --> 00:31:45,740
并且我打算继续调查他告诉我的事儿
And I intend to follow up on what he told me.

376
00:31:45,741 --> 00:31:47,405
记住 中校 
Try to remember, Colonel, 

377
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:48,980
你在这里的职责是机密
that your function here is covert,

378
00:31:48,981 --> 00:31:50,942
我们希望你办事
which means we want to hear as little as possible

379
00:31:50,943 --> 00:31:53,701
越低调越好
about what you get up to.

380
00:31:53,702 --> 00:31:55,982
你看起来可不怎么样 你还好吧
You don't look well. Are you all right?

381
00:31:55,983 --> 00:31:57,621
有点头痛
A slight headache.

382
00:31:57,622 --> 00:32:00,542
嗯 我觉得你是在装样子
Well, I presume you're in some sort of disguise.

383
00:32:00,543 --> 00:32:03,742
如果没有 那么我就把我裁缝的名字告诉你
If not, let me get you the name of my tailor.

384
00:32:08,742 --> 00:32:11,340
我一直向往南非  
I was hoping for South Africa. 

385
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:12,981
我已经申请了签证
I already applied for a visa.

386
00:32:12,982 --> 00:32:14,901
这可不明智
That was unwise.

387
00:32:14,902 --> 00:32:17,180
一旦被盖世太保发现
If the Gestapo found out, that might explain why

388
00:32:17,181 --> 00:32:18,982
他们逮捕你时就有了个好理由
they tried to snatch you when they did.

389
00:32:18,983 --> 00:32:21,649
但你能把我带到那  是吧  
But you can get me there? Yes? 

390
00:32:21,649 --> 00:32:23,261
一个全新的生活
A new life?

391
00:32:23,262 --> 00:32:26,301
不  德国特工会等着你的
No. German agents will be waiting for you.

392
00:32:26,302 --> 00:32:28,262
你得去法国的某处
It has to be somewhere French.

393
00:32:28,263 --> 00:32:30,101
或许是加拿大
Canada perhaps.

394
00:32:30,102 --> 00:32:32,221
加拿大
Canada?

395
00:32:32,222 --> 00:32:36,022
伯爵夫人有可能在那儿与我碰头吗
Would it be possible for the Countess to join me there?

396
00:32:38,462 --> 00:32:40,421
Uhl先生
Herr Uhl...

397
00:32:40,422 --> 00:32:43,221
她不是伯爵夫人
she's not a Countess.

398
00:32:43,222 --> 00:32:45,262
她也不曾爱过你
Nor was she ever in love with you.

399
00:32:53,222 --> 00:32:55,061
他清醒了 是不
He's awake, then?

400
00:32:55,062 --> 00:32:56,740
认清了他生活的事实
Awake to the facts of life.

401
00:32:56,741 --> 00:32:59,055
官方报道 他死于因窒息
Officially, he died of cardiac arrest,

402
00:32:59,056 --> 00:33:00,700
引起的心脏骤停
brought on by asphyxiation.

403
00:33:00,701 --> 00:33:02,982
这样应该可以摆脱德国方面的追踪
That should throw the Germans off the trail.

404
00:33:02,983 --> 00:33:04,062
十分感谢
Thank you.

405
00:33:06,342 --> 00:33:08,700
你注意过这儿的护士有多年轻么
Have you noticed how young these nurses are?

406
00:33:08,701 --> 00:33:10,740
或者只是说我们在渐渐老去
Or is it just that we're getting older?

407
00:33:10,741 --> 00:33:12,062
恐怕是吧 Antoni
I'm afraid so, Antoni.

408
00:33:27,142 --> 00:33:30,782
{\pos(191,280)}我刚收到了一封来自华沙的电报

409
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:32,701
{\pos(191,280)}Uhl死了

410
00:33:32,702 --> 00:33:36,701
{\pos(191,280)}你不仅搞砸了他的绑架

411
00:33:36,702 --> 00:33:40,800
{\pos(191,280)}你该死的还杀了他

412
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:41,981
{\pos(191,280)}白痴!

413
00:33:41,982 --> 00:33:43,257
{\pos(191,280)}我简直不能相信 

414
00:33:43,257 --> 00:33:44,702
{\pos(191,280)}Sturmbannfuehrer先生

415
00:33:44,703 --> 00:33:46,821
{\pos(191,280)}去看看他的遗孀

416
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,002
{\pos(191,280)}以表我们的慰问和哀思?

417
00:33:49,503 --> 00:33:50,621
{\pos(191,280)}不 你这蠢货

418
00:33:51,522 --> 00:33:53,000
{\pos(191,280)}去把房子搜个底朝天

419
00:33:55,582 --> 00:33:58,000
{\pos(191,280)}你在藏什么呢 Zoller

420
00:33:59,000 --> 00:33:59,999
{\pos(191,280)}难不成你是犹太人

421
00:34:09,902 --> 00:34:11,422
一些拼图被弄丢了
Some pieces are missing.

422
00:34:11,423 --> 00:34:14,982
我找不到这块 哪儿都找不到
I can't find this one, I can't find it anywhere.

423
00:34:17,022 --> 00:34:18,662
你睡眠好点儿了吗
Are you sleeping better?

424
00:34:20,342 --> 00:34:21,821
并不怎么样
Not really.

425
00:34:21,822 --> 00:34:26,021
他们待我并不是很好 你知道的
They don't treat me very well here, you know.

426
00:34:26,022 --> 00:34:27,935
那些年轻人似乎忘记了
The younger ones seem to forget that 

427
00:34:27,935 --> 00:34:29,020
这儿曾经是我的房子
this was my house once.

428
00:34:29,021 --> 00:34:31,502
如果我能的话 他们估计全都要被解雇了
And if it was, I'd dismiss most of them.

429
00:34:34,222 --> 00:34:35,701
华沙怎么样
How's Warsaw?

430
00:34:35,702 --> 00:34:38,221
阴冷潮湿
Cold and wet.

431
00:34:38,222 --> 00:34:40,901
遇到了真命天子么?
Is there a man in your life?

432
00:34:40,902 --> 00:34:42,941
我给你说过Max
I've told you about Max.

433
00:34:42,942 --> 00:34:45,701
噢 他还蒙受你青眼?
Oh, he's still in the picture?

434
00:34:45,702 --> 00:34:47,461
是啊 母亲
Yes, Mother.

435
00:34:47,988 --> 00:34:49,512
嗯 我搞不懂你为什么
Well, I wonder why 

436
00:34:49,512 --> 00:34:50,780
从来不带他来见我
it is you've never brought him here to see me.

437
00:34:50,781 --> 00:34:52,622
因为你不喜欢俄罗斯人
Because you don't like Russians.

438
00:34:52,623 --> 00:34:54,862
呃 这是事实  还有德国人
Well, that's true. Or Germans.

439
00:34:56,102 --> 00:34:58,136
如果我们还呆在巴黎的话 
If we'd stayed in Paris, 

440
00:34:58,136 --> 00:34:59,662
现在你已经和某个法国人结婚了
you'd be married to a Frenchman by now.

441
00:35:01,422 --> 00:35:03,701
我最近见着了一个
I met one recently.

442
00:35:03,702 --> 00:35:05,821
他似乎被我迷住了
He seemed quite taken with me.

443
00:35:05,822 --> 00:35:07,381
他有土地么
Does he have land?

444
00:35:07,382 --> 00:35:09,581
不清楚
I've no idea.

445
00:35:09,582 --> 00:35:10,703
嗯 他们经常装作
Well, they often pretend

446
00:35:10,704 --> 00:35:12,900
自己封邑无数 等到最后却是一贫如洗
they do and then they turn out to be penniless.

447
00:35:12,901 --> 00:35:14,702
我是说 你的俄罗斯小伙没有钱
I mean, your Russian doesn't have money.

448
00:35:19,782 --> 00:35:23,142
我需要一块带些绿色的蓝天拼图
I need a piece of blue sky with a little bit of green.

449
00:35:35,102 --> 00:35:37,220
德国人在试图抓捕Uhl先生
The Germans tried to snatch Herr Uhl.

450
00:35:37,221 --> 00:35:39,022
也许是盖世太保在盯着他
It could be the Gestapo is onto him.

451
00:35:39,023 --> 00:35:41,061
他们可能已经知道你了
They may know about you.

452
00:35:41,062 --> 00:35:42,793
如果他们知道 他们会去寻找
If so, they'll be looking

453
00:35:42,794 --> 00:35:44,740
Potocki伯爵夫人 
for the Countess Potocki, 

454
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:45,702
而不是Olga Musser
not Olga Musser.

455
00:35:45,703 --> 00:35:48,261
即便如此 我们也要做到未雨绸缪
Even so, we should take precautions.

456
00:35:48,262 --> 00:35:49,901
于是派来一个保镖
A bodyguard, perhaps?

457
00:35:50,248 --> 00:35:52,075
高挑英俊又对某一年龄段的女性
Tall and handsome with a soft spot 

458
00:35:52,075 --> 00:35:52,862
情有独钟
for women of a certain age?

459
00:35:52,863 --> 00:35:55,221
Olga 请认真对待这事
Olga, please treat this seriously.

460
00:35:55,222 --> 00:35:58,102
收拾收拾东西 搬去这家旅店里住几天
Take some things, move to this hotel for a few days.

461
00:35:59,222 --> 00:36:00,681
就在Sienna大街 
It's on Sienna Street, 

462
00:36:00,681 --> 00:36:02,500
离Cleo咖啡厅不远
not far from the Cafe Cleo.

463
00:36:02,501 --> 00:36:04,822
预约时我用了你的真实姓名
The reservation's under your real name.

464
00:36:06,382 --> 00:36:07,542
那么不再是伯爵夫人了
So no more Countess?

465
00:36:09,022 --> 00:36:10,382
我会怀念她的
I shall miss her.

466
00:36:23,022 --> 00:36:25,234
我最近没有见到你 Lapp博士  
I haven't seen you of late, Dr Lapp. 

467
00:36:25,234 --> 00:36:25,822
你去旅行了
Have you been travelling?

468
00:36:25,823 --> 00:36:29,861
柏林 出席我公司的销售会议
Berlin, for my company's sales conference.

469
00:36:29,862 --> 00:36:31,541
在那期间
While I was there,

470
00:36:31,542 --> 00:36:34,662
温莎公爵和夫人去拜访了希特勒先生
the Duke and Duchess of Windsor visited Herr Hitler.

471
00:36:34,663 --> 00:36:37,941
微笑 握手 再挥手
Smiles, handshakes and waves.

472
00:36:37,942 --> 00:36:40,380
英国人也被他蛊惑了不成
Are the English falling under his spell too?

473
00:36:40,381 --> 00:36:42,462
你不赞同现政权
You don't approve of the present regime?

474
00:36:42,463 --> 00:36:46,541
古老欧洲的文化 礼仪 稳定
The culture of old Europe, civility, stability...

475
00:36:46,542 --> 00:36:49,221
对德国来说可不是个坏事
was not such a bad thing for Germany.

476
00:36:49,222 --> 00:36:52,261
我们德国人也许并不像你想的
Some of us Germans may not be

477
00:36:52,262 --> 00:36:55,302
那样像法国的敌人
so much the enemy of France as you might think.

478
00:37:01,022 --> 00:37:02,220
抱歉 您刚才说什么
Sorry, you were saying?

479
00:37:02,221 --> 00:37:03,316
没关系  
Don't worry. 

480
00:37:03,316 --> 00:37:05,622
美丽的女士同样总会吸引我的目光
A beautiful woman always catches my eye too.

481
00:37:05,623 --> 00:37:07,301
你认识她
You know her?

482
00:37:07,302 --> 00:37:09,220
我们最近见过一面  我 我应该向她问声好
We met recently. I... I should say hello.

483
00:37:09,221 --> 00:37:12,180
当然  若一切顺利 我想我该说再见了
Of course. And if it goes well, I will say goodbye.

484
00:37:12,181 --> 00:37:13,982
见到你总是很愉快 Lapp博士
Always good to see you, Dr Lapp.

485
00:37:18,742 --> 00:37:21,861
我能否与你同桌?  还是说你在等Max
May I? Or is Max joining you?

486
00:37:21,862 --> 00:37:24,742
不  Max正在忙着赶文章
No. Max is finishing an article.

487
00:37:28,222 --> 00:37:30,540
我来这儿是为了避雨
I came here to get out of the rain.

488
00:37:30,541 --> 00:37:31,742
我去了电影院
I've been to the cinema.

489
00:37:31,743 --> 00:37:32,901
去看什么
To see what?

490
00:37:32,902 --> 00:37:34,951
Laurel和Hardy的片子  
Laurel and Hardy. 

491
00:37:34,951 --> 00:37:35,661
大闹玩具城
Babes In Toyland.

492
00:37:35,662 --> 00:37:37,781
我需要一些欢笑
I needed a laugh.

493
00:37:37,782 --> 00:37:39,222
你为什么不开心
What made you sad?

494
00:37:40,222 --> 00:37:42,301
我母亲的情况不是很好
My mother is unwell.

495
00:37:42,302 --> 00:37:44,862
自我父亲去世起她就没有好起来过了
She's never been quite right since my father died.

496
00:37:45,982 --> 00:37:48,421
她怀念过去的奢华时光
She misses the grand old days.

497
00:37:48,422 --> 00:37:50,862
她接受不了自己有一个工作的女儿
She can't believe she has a daughter who works.

498
00:37:50,863 --> 00:37:53,461
所以你的童年生活优越?
So you had a privileged childhood?

499
00:37:53,462 --> 00:37:55,142
和你比就不算什么了
Not compared to you.

500
00:37:57,022 --> 00:37:59,382
这戒指难道不代表着你是一位贵族
Doesn't this ring mean you're nobility?

501
00:37:59,383 --> 00:38:01,341
噢 只是个卑微的骑士罢了
Oh, just a lowly chevalier.

502
00:38:02,604 --> 00:38:04,177
效忠于国王的骑士 
A knight in service to the king - 

503
00:38:04,177 --> 00:38:05,102
在法国还有国王的时候
when France had a king.

504
00:38:05,103 --> 00:38:07,861
不过  仍是我唯一认识的贵族
Still... the only one I've ever known.

505
00:38:07,862 --> 00:38:10,582
你一直在检查我
You've been checking up on me.

506
00:38:16,302 --> 00:38:17,902
是的 我回来了 亲爱的们
Yes, I'm home, my darlings.

507
00:38:27,902 --> 00:38:31,261
这些信件 大多都是账单
These letters - bills mostly -

508
00:38:31,262 --> 00:38:33,542
全是寄给Olga Musser的
are addressed to Olga Musser.

509
00:38:38,742 --> 00:38:41,902
那么是谁出主意让你变成一个伯爵夫人
So whose idea was it to make you a Countess?

510
00:38:50,142 --> 00:38:52,582
我简直不能相信现在有多晚了
I can't believe how late it is.

511
00:38:54,622 --> 00:38:56,182
Max会伤心吗
Will Max be upset?

512
00:38:58,428 --> 00:38:59,876
如果知道你带我去了个那么棒的餐厅
He might be upset that 

513
00:38:59,876 --> 00:39:01,862
他一定会沮丧的
you took me to such a fine restaurant

514
00:39:01,863 --> 00:39:05,701
并且你还点了那么好的红酒
and that you ordered some very good wine.

515
00:39:05,702 --> 00:39:08,542
人生得意须尽欢 莫使金樽空对月
Life's too short to drink bad wine.

516
00:39:10,662 --> 00:39:12,821
谢谢了
Thank you.

517
00:39:12,822 --> 00:39:15,702
谢谢你让我重拾笑容
And thank you for making me smile.

518
00:39:18,662 --> 00:39:20,582
什么时候我才能再见到你
When can I see you again?

519
00:39:24,102 --> 00:39:26,582
也许不如不见的好
Maybe it's better if we don't.

520
00:39:28,982 --> 00:39:31,062
我认为 欢愉不过再相逢
I think it might be better if we do.

521
00:39:39,182 --> 00:39:41,822
晚安 Jean-Francois
Good night, Jean-Francois.

522
00:40:17,702 --> 00:40:19,861
写完了么
Did you finish it?

523
00:40:19,862 --> 00:40:21,582
没什么价值
For what it's worth.

524
00:40:23,982 --> 00:40:25,781
都是些废话  我没机会再写
Chit-chat. I don't have the

525
00:40:25,782 --> 00:40:28,580
正儿八经的东西了
chance to write anything serious any more.

526
00:40:28,581 --> 00:40:30,982
就算我可以 我还有什么好写的呢
And if I did, would I have anything to say?

527
00:40:33,462 --> 00:40:35,589
你是一个很棒的作家 Max  
You're a brilliant writer, Max. 

528
00:40:35,589 --> 00:40:37,741
只是要静候良机
Just bide your time.

529
00:40:37,742 --> 00:40:40,341
也许我应该去趟英格兰
Maybe I should go to England.

530
00:40:40,342 --> 00:40:43,261
他们可能会在公园里给我一个街头演说台
They might give me a soapbox in the park.

531
00:40:43,262 --> 00:40:46,208
每逢周六我就可以愤怒地反对斯大林  
On Saturdays, I can rage against Stalin. 

532
00:40:46,208 --> 00:40:48,022
到了周日是希特勒
On Sundays, Hitler.

