这些话我都听过了 Max
I've heard it all before, Max.

713
00:53:20,423 --> 00:53:22,782
老天啊 这可是圣诞节
For God's sake, it's Christmas.

714
00:53:30,462 --> 00:53:34,022
啊 见着你可真好  还有你 你看上去不错
Ah, good to see you. And you, you look very well.

715
00:53:47,142 --> 00:53:49,621
你的假期怎么样 中校
How was your holiday, Colonel?

716
00:53:49,622 --> 00:53:51,581
非常愉快
Very pleasant.

717
00:53:51,582 --> 00:53:53,982
我和我姐姐待在乡下和巴黎城里
I was with my sister in the country and also Paris.

718
00:53:53,983 --> 00:53:55,941
真羡慕你在巴黎
I envy you Paris.

719
00:53:55,942 --> 00:53:57,542
贵国那边事态如何
How are things in the motherland?

720
00:53:57,543 --> 00:53:59,701
目前尚艰难
Difficult at present.

721
00:53:59,702 --> 00:54:01,221
那些试验
The trials.

722
00:54:01,222 --> 00:54:03,542
我们被召回了
We have been recalled.

723
00:54:05,022 --> 00:54:06,941
也许是升职吧
Promotion, perhaps?

724
00:54:06,942 --> 00:54:08,581
更像是一发子弹
More likely a bullet.

725
00:54:08,582 --> 00:54:12,421
斯大林在清除所有的老布尔什维克党
Stalin is purging all the old Bolsheviks.

726
00:54:12,422 --> 00:54:13,741
你能帮助我们吗
Can you help us?

727
00:54:13,742 --> 00:54:16,901
我们喜欢你 你知道的 中校
We like you, as you know, Colonel.

728
00:54:16,902 --> 00:54:18,781
但我们总觉得
But we always felt...

729
00:54:18,782 --> 00:54:22,501
你在这儿的职责比
that your function here was more...

730
00:54:22,502 --> 00:54:24,981
外交更秘密
clandestine than diplomatic.

731
00:54:24,982 --> 00:54:28,300
并且我们理解你期望着能有所回报
And we understand you would expect something in return.

732
00:54:28,301 --> 00:54:30,022
为了让你离开波兰
For getting you out of Poland?

733
00:54:31,062 --> 00:54:33,541
你们被监视了么  就在这儿
Are you being watched? Here?

734
00:54:33,542 --> 00:54:35,621
我们没法说
We can't say.

735
00:54:35,622 --> 00:54:38,620
他们非常善于隐匿自己不被发现
They're very good at it when they don't want you to know.

736
00:54:38,621 --> 00:54:40,980
我得去贝尔格莱德呆几天
I have to go to Belgrade for a few days.

737
00:54:40,981 --> 00:54:43,942
- 等我回来再说吧   - 别拖太久
- Let's talk when I return. - Don't wait too long.

738
00:54:47,022 --> 00:54:49,381
这趟旅行是Jourdain的主意吗
Was this trip Jourdain's idea?

739
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:50,464
当然  
Of course. 

740
00:54:50,464 --> 00:54:52,102
他会尽其所能把你从局里带出来的
He'll do anything to get you out of the office.

741
00:54:52,103 --> 00:54:54,341
这算是一个安慰
But there is one consolation.

742
00:54:54,342 --> 00:54:56,141
一月份去贝尔格莱德?
For Belgrade in January?

743
00:54:56,142 --> 00:54:58,333
这是国际联盟的会议  
It's a League of Nations conference. 

744
00:54:58,333 --> 00:54:59,340
所以Anna会在场
So Anna will be there.

745
00:54:59,341 --> 00:55:01,342
她甚至有可能在你的火车上
She may even be on your train.

746
00:55:43,809 --> 00:55:44,559
晚餐上你想要
Would you prefer 

747
00:55:44,559 --> 00:55:46,140
首席还是次席 Colonel
the first or second seating for dinner, Colonel?

748
00:55:46,141 --> 00:55:49,382
Skarbek小姐选择哪种席位了?
Which seating is Mademoiselle Skarbek down for?

749
00:55:51,302 --> 00:55:53,821
这位女士不在名单内 先生
The lady's not listed, sir.

750
00:55:53,822 --> 00:55:55,062
那么要次席
The second, then.

751
00:56:17,822 --> 00:56:19,462
还要点别的么 先生
You prefer something else, sir?

752
00:56:19,463 --> 00:56:21,422
一杯人头马
Just a Remy Martin.

753
00:56:29,822 --> 00:56:32,421
Anna
Anna!

754
00:56:32,422 --> 00:56:34,741
我在找你  你去哪了
I looked for you. Where were you?

755
00:56:34,742 --> 00:56:36,942
我和一些同事去了克拉科夫
I got on at Krakow with some colleagues.

756
00:56:36,943 --> 00:56:39,262
我还单独进餐  真是浪费
And I dined alone. What a waste.

757
00:56:40,262 --> 00:56:41,302
请坐吧
Please...

758
00:56:47,422 --> 00:56:48,941
你要去哪儿
Where are you going?

759
00:56:48,942 --> 00:56:50,861
和你去同一个会议
The same conference as you.

760
00:56:50,862 --> 00:56:52,861
我怀疑它能起到什么好作用
I doubt it will do any good.

761
00:56:52,862 --> 00:56:55,022
还有人听国联的话么
Does anyone listen to the League any more?

762
00:56:55,023 --> 00:56:58,381
尤其现在墨索里尼带着意大利退出了
Especially now Mussolini's pulled Italy out.

763
00:56:58,382 --> 00:57:00,102
你希望知道什么呢
What do you hope to learn?

764
00:57:01,422 --> 00:57:02,459
老实说 
To be honest, 

765
00:57:02,459 --> 00:57:04,902
在听说你也在那儿之前我也打算请辞这差事的
I intended to bow out till I heard you'd be there.

766
00:57:06,062 --> 00:57:09,661
你脑子里在想什么  一场火车上的罗曼史?
What did you have in mind? An adventure on a train?

767
00:57:09,662 --> 00:57:11,581
不是
No.

768
00:57:11,582 --> 00:57:13,861
更多
More.

769
00:57:13,862 --> 00:57:15,582
我在追求你 Anna
I'm pursuing you, Anna.

770
00:57:18,702 --> 00:57:20,581
你知道我的处境
You know my situation.

771
00:57:20,582 --> 00:57:21,782
是的 我知道
Yes, I do.

772
00:57:23,102 --> 00:57:24,782
这毫无影响
Makes no difference.

773
00:57:28,622 --> 00:57:30,622
我们还几乎不了解对方
We hardly know each other.

774
00:58:30,102 --> 00:58:32,501
你觉着我们到哪儿了
Where do you think we are?

775
00:58:32,502 --> 00:58:34,022
下一站是布达佩斯
The next stop's Budapest.

776
00:58:35,222 --> 00:58:37,582
我宁愿谈谈华沙
I'd rather talk about Warsaw.

777
00:58:40,062 --> 00:58:42,422
我爱上你了 Anna
I'm in love with you, Anna.

778
00:58:43,782 --> 00:58:45,582
我都忘了这种感觉了
I'd forgotten these feelings.

779
00:58:47,622 --> 00:58:50,261
你确定
Are you sure about this?

780
00:58:50,262 --> 00:58:52,020
世事多变
With the way things are in the world,

781
00:58:52,021 --> 00:58:54,022
这是我唯一能确定的事情
it's the only thing I AM sure about.

782
00:58:56,022 --> 00:58:58,902
并且我不相信你是爱Max的
And I don't believe you're in love with Max.

783
00:59:01,702 --> 00:59:05,462
你并不知道我对Max的感情
You have no idea about my feelings for Max!

784
00:59:06,942 --> 00:59:08,022
我曾漂泊不定
I was adrift.

785
00:59:09,502 --> 00:59:11,662
他将我引入这项工作
He pushed me to take this job.

786
00:59:13,702 --> 00:59:16,861
他让我感觉到我是有用的
He made me feel useful...

787
00:59:16,862 --> 00:59:18,742
很有用的人
relevant.

788
00:59:20,942 --> 00:59:22,782
Max是我的锚
Max is my anchor.

789
00:59:25,702 --> 00:59:27,542
现在无法安定的人是我
Then it's me who's adrift.

790
00:59:30,142 --> 00:59:32,062
你必须给我时间
You must give me time.

791
00:59:34,062 --> 00:59:35,662
去结束这一切
To end it my way.

792
00:59:50,702 --> 00:59:53,102
你被监视了 我的朋友
You're under surveillance, my friend.

793
00:59:53,103 --> 00:59:56,981
并不是高等级别的 我们很容易发现他们
Not very high-grade, we spotted them quite easily.

794
00:59:56,982 --> 00:59:58,541
他们
"Them"?

795
00:59:58,542 --> 01:00:01,302
一个四人的队伍 所以他们很谨慎
A team of four, so they are taking it seriously.

796
01:00:02,382 --> 01:00:03,834
一个乌克兰人 
One's Ukrainian, 

797
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:06,580
其他三个是德裔波兰人
the other three are Poles, of German extraction.

798
01:00:06,581 --> 01:00:09,284
他们中是不是有一个尖嘴猴腮的 
Does one of them have a pinched face, 

799
01:00:09,284 --> 01:00:10,860
像一只好斗的黄鼠狼
like a fierce weasel?

800
01:00:11,263 --> 01:00:12,388
你见过他们   
You've seen him before?  

801
01:00:12,388 --> 01:00:14,341
是啊  Uhl被绑架的那一天
Yeah. The day Uhl was abducted.

802
01:00:14,342 --> 01:00:16,096
就是他  他们在看着呢
That's him. They are watching

803
01:00:16,097 --> 01:00:18,940
不论在公寓里还是出门你都被监视了
your apartment and tailing you when you go out.

804
01:00:20,219 --> 01:00:21,727
我想你知道我和Anna 
I suppose you know things are heating up 

805
01:00:21,727 --> 01:00:22,622
Skarbek的关系
between Anna Skarbek

806
01:00:22,623 --> 01:00:24,301
正在升温
and me.

807
01:00:24,302 --> 01:00:28,542
我听说了  上星期她不是留宿两次了么
I had heard. Didn't she stay over twice last week?

808
01:00:30,102 --> 01:00:32,262
我想让她搬过来同住
I want her to move in with me.

809
01:00:33,963 --> 01:00:36,189
一个曾经和一个有着可疑声誉的
A woman who was formerly living in

810
01:00:36,189 --> 01:00:37,102
俄罗斯流亡者
sin with a Russian emigre

811
01:00:37,103 --> 01:00:39,101
同居的女人
of dubious reputation?

812
01:00:39,102 --> 01:00:42,102
这足够把你的上司吓得尿裤子了
That should make your superiors piss their pantaloons!

813
01:00:49,302 --> 01:00:54,181
Max很脆弱  你还不懂么
Max is fragile. Can't you understand?

814
01:00:54,182 --> 01:00:57,861
他感觉 无家可归
He feels... displaced.

815
01:00:57,862 --> 01:00:59,804
一无所有  
Dispossessed. 

816
01:00:59,804 --> 01:01:01,901
一旦我离开了 他就完全孤身一人了
When I leave, he'll be completely alone.

817
01:01:01,902 --> 01:01:04,101
所以你还没有告诉他么
So you still haven't told him?

818
01:01:04,102 --> 01:01:06,781
还没有 我需要拿捏好时间
Not yet, I have to pick my moment.

819
01:01:06,782 --> 01:01:10,701
我们的生活并不像在你床上一样简单
Our lives aren't as simple as they are in your bed.

820
01:01:10,702 --> 01:01:13,022
我们的生活从来不简单
Our lives will never be simple.

821
01:01:24,702 --> 01:01:26,301
是谁
Who is it?

822
01:01:26,302 --> 01:01:28,782
Malka Rozen  求你了中校 
Malka Rozen. Please, Colonel, 

823
01:01:28,782 --> 01:01:30,146
让我进去
let me in!

824
01:01:35,902 --> 01:01:39,141
噢 老天  他受伤了
Oh, God! He's hurt!

825
01:01:39,528 --> 01:01:42,014
Viktor  我们来这的路上  
Viktor. We were on our way here. 

826
01:01:42,481 --> 01:01:43,461
他们知道了!
They know!

827
01:01:43,462 --> 01:01:46,101
他在冰上滑倒伤到了脚踝   
He fell on the ice and hurt his ankle. 

828
01:01:46,101 --> 01:01:46,670
在哪儿
Where?

829
01:01:46,670 --> 01:01:48,247
那个小公园里   
In the small park. 

830
01:01:48,247 --> 01:01:49,178
教堂边的广场上?
In the square by the church?

831
01:01:49,178 --> 01:01:50,781
是的 对 那有个教堂
Yes, yes, there is a church!

832
01:01:51,545 --> 01:01:53,497
Wlada 带Rozen夫人去厨房 
Wlada, take Madame Rozen into the kitchen 

833
01:01:53,497 --> 01:01:54,212
泡些茶
and make some tea.

834
01:01:59,262 --> 01:02:01,377
那是谁  发生什么事了   
Who is it? What's going on? 

835
01:02:01,377 --> 01:02:02,262
出事了  我得走了
There's a problem. I have to go out.

836
01:02:07,106 --> 01:02:08,346
我走后 就把门关好 
When I leave, lock the door behind me 

837
01:02:08,346 --> 01:02:09,462
别给任何人开门
and don't open it for anyone.

838
01:03:08,100 --> 01:03:08,954
没事了 没事了
It's all right, it's all right,

839
01:03:08,954 --> 01:03:10,827
- Viktor   - 他们知道  
- Viktor. - They know,  

840
01:03:11,271 --> 01:03:11,990
上校 他们知道了
Colonel.They know.

841
01:03:11,990 --> 01:03:13,822
好了 好了 没事 来吧
All right, all right, all right. Come on.

842
01:03:13,823 --> 01:03:17,422
别担心  我会搞定的
Don't worry. Don't worry. I'll take care of it.

843
01:03:21,462 --> 01:03:23,182
谢谢你
Thank you.

844
01:03:34,718 --> 01:03:35,823
为什么是今晚 Viktor  
Why tonight, Viktor? 

845
01:03:35,823 --> 01:03:36,475
发生什么事了
What happened?

846
01:03:37,582 --> 01:03:41,341
大使馆临时召开晚间会议
A late meeting was called at the Embassy.

847
01:03:41,342 --> 01:03:43,981
我们的一个朋友
One of our friends...

848
01:03:43,982 --> 01:03:47,381
一个很好的老朋友
a good friend from the old days...

849
01:03:47,382 --> 01:03:49,741
突然不肯跟我们说话了
suddenly wouldn't talk to us.

850
01:03:49,742 --> 01:03:52,061
他都看在眼里
It was in his eyes.

851
01:03:52,062 --> 01:03:54,422
他被审问了 我们能感觉得到
He'd been questioned, we could feel it.

852
01:03:56,262 --> 01:04:00,261
我们知道  我们甚至都没回家取我们的东西
We knew. We didn't even go home to get our things.

853
01:04:00,262 --> 01:04:02,142
好了 继续走吧  没多远了
Right, keep walking. Not far.

854
01:04:03,342 --> 01:04:05,102
你半辈子都在为他们干活
You work half your life for them.

855
01:04:05,103 --> 01:04:08,621
25年的服务 公忠体国
25 years of service, faith and obedience.

856
01:04:09,236 --> 01:04:10,839
到现在你还会
And still you're afraid of 

857
01:04:10,839 --> 01:04:12,982
害怕半夜的敲门声
the knock on the door at midnight.

858
01:04:14,502 --> 01:04:17,382
怎么停下了
Why have we stopped?

859
01:04:45,862 --> 01:04:48,141
他是谁 Vicktor
Who was he, Viktor?

860
01:04:48,142 --> 01:04:49,622
我不知道
I wouldn't know.

861
01:04:56,622 --> 01:04:58,862
Anna 是我
Anna, it's me.

862
01:05:03,244 --> 01:05:05,104
Viktor  你还好吗   
Viktor! Are you all right? 

863
01:05:05,104 --> 01:05:06,777
他冻僵了  Wlada 烧热水
He's frozen. Wlada, run a hot bath.

864
01:05:06,777 --> 01:05:08,940
有多热就多热  再拿些干衣服来
As hot as you can get it. And some dry clothes.

865
01:05:08,941 --> 01:05:10,462
我能做什么  我能帮什么忙吗
What can I do? Can I help?

866
01:05:12,574 --> 01:05:13,768
你现在必须回家 Anna  
You must go home now, Anna. 

867
01:05:14,458 --> 01:05:15,758
你什么都没看见
And you saw none of this.

868
01:05:35,742 --> 01:05:38,020
看在老天的面上 带他们到大使馆
For God's sake, bring them to the Embassy!

869
01:05:38,021 --> 01:05:40,542
冒着跟苏联政府发生外交冲突的危险吗
Risk a diplomatic confrontation with the Soviets?

870
01:05:40,543 --> 01:05:42,741
巴黎方面会想解决这个的
Paris will want to handle this.

871
01:05:42,742 --> 01:05:44,147
巴黎能足够快地搞定他们
Paris will get them soon enough.

872
01:05:44,148 --> 01:05:45,860
找架私人飞机带他们到那
Find a private plane to get them there.

873
01:05:45,861 --> 01:05:47,488
我们必须把这事揽自己身上
We have to keep this to ourselves.

874
01:05:47,489 --> 01:05:49,260
我们不能冒让波兰人尴尬的危险
We can't risk embarrassing the Poles.

875
01:05:49,261 --> 01:05:51,174
你不应该自己一个人管这事的
You shouldn't be running this alone.

876
01:05:51,175 --> 01:05:52,822
他们为我而来  他们信任我
They came to me. They trust me.

877
01:05:52,823 --> 01:05:55,022
你的伯爵夫人也信任你
So did your Countess.

878
01:05:56,742 --> 01:05:58,340
- 你带了几个人   - 两个
- How many are with you? - Two.

879
01:05:58,341 --> 01:05:59,912
一个安排在后街 一个安排在
Put one in the back alley, one on

880
01:05:59,913 --> 01:06:02,342
楼梯上 你守前门  带家伙了吗
the stairs and you out front. Do you have a weapon?

881
01:06:03,902 --> 01:06:05,462
好极了  行动吧
Good. Don't hesitate.

882
01:06:07,902 --> 01:06:11,221
我们在等谁  我们的德国朋友吗
Who are we expecting? Our German friends?

883
01:06:11,222 --> 01:06:13,102
不是的 是俄国人  苏联内务人民委员会的
No, these are Russians. NKVD.

884
01:06:13,103 --> 01:06:16,182
那敢情好啊
Oh. It will be a pleasure.

885
01:06:56,742 --> 01:06:59,141
我们和法国之间没有什么
We had little to do with France.

886
01:06:59,142 --> 01:07:01,742
我们行动集中在波兰人身上
Our operations were centred on the Poles.

887
01:07:01,743 --> 01:07:05,421
尤其是对社会党的渗透上
Especially penetration of the socialist parties.

888
01:07:05,422 --> 01:07:08,581
莫斯科总部看中这个
Moscow Central is obsessed with this.

889
01:07:08,582 --> 01:07:10,981
我们做的与他人无异
We did what everyone does.

890
01:07:10,982 --> 01:07:15,141
作战计划 武器生产 政治诽谤
War plans, arms production, political personalities,

891
01:07:15,142 --> 01:07:17,101
边境防御
border defences.

892
01:07:17,102 --> 01:07:21,181
我觉得这和你的工作差远了 中校
I doubt it's much different from what you do, Colonel.

893
01:07:21,182 --> 01:07:22,981
德国的情报网呢
Any German networks?

894
01:07:22,982 --> 01:07:24,699
我们还没掌握他们  
